<section class="section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Drip for Cotton</span>
            <h2>SDI Solves Cotton's Biggest Irrigation Challenges</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="cloud"></i></div>
                <h3>No Rank Growth</h3>
                <p>Furrow and flood irrigation often deliver excess early-season water that promotes vegetative over-development ("rank growth") — taller plants that shade bolls and are harder to defoliate. SDI delivers exactly the planned deficit.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="shield"></i></div>
                <h3>Boll Rot Reduction</h3>
                <p>Boll rot thrives in wet, high-humidity canopy conditions created by surface irrigation. SDI keeps the soil surface dry and the canopy open — dramatically reducing boll rot pressure without fungicide applications.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="thermometer"></i></div>
                <h3>Cutout Deficit Precision</h3>
                <p>The regulated deficit irrigation (RDI) applied after NAWF-5 (cutout) is critical for fiber maturity and micronaire. SDI provides the precise control needed to execute the correct stress at exactly the right time.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="tractor"></i></div>
                <h3>Cleaner Harvest</h3>
                <p>Drip-irrigated cotton fields are firm and free of surface irrigation ruts — reducing harvest losses and keeping trash out of the module. GPS-guided pickers work more efficiently in clean SDI fields.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon"><i data-lucide="sprout"></i></div>
                <h3>Plant Growth Regulator Efficiency</h3>
                <p>PGR timing and efficacy are closely linked to soil moisture. SDI's consistent moisture baseline makes PGR programs more predictable and effective than when applied under variable furrow conditions.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="highlight-card">
                <div class="highlight-card-icon"><i data-lucide="bar-chart-2"></i></div>
                <h3>Case Study: West Texas</h3>
                <p>A 2,200-acre Texas dryland-converted SDI operation reduced applied water from 24" to 12" per season while improving average lint yield from 780 to 950 lbs/acre and improving micronaire from 3.9 to 4.2.</p>
                <a href="/growers-stories" class="btn-primary-sm" style="margin-top:16px;">Read More →</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

