<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="two-col-layout">
            <div>
                <span class="section-eyebrow">System Design</span>
                <h2>Cotton SDI Design Essentials</h2>
                <ul class="check-list" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <li>Lateral spacing: 30–40 inches (one lateral between twin rows)</li>
                    <li>Installation depth: 10–14 inches below the soil surface</li>
                    <li>Emitter spacing: 8–12 inches for medium-textured soils</li>
                    <li>Flow rates: 0.16–0.32 GPH to match soil infiltration</li>
                    <li>Pressure compensation for sloped fields in the rolling plains</li>
                    <li>Fertigation compatible with UAN, KTS, and PGR programs</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:28px;display:inline-block;">Find a Dealer</a>
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="info-card" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
                    <h3>Recommended: DripSmart RowCrop SDI</h3>
                    <p>40-inch spacing variant, with anti-siphon emitters and root-intrusion protection rated for 20+ years in cotton rotation. Compatible with standard 40" row configurations.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="info-card">
                    <h3>DripSphere OS Cotton Module</h3>
                    <p>Heat unit–based irrigation scheduling with NAWF tracking for cutout timing, boll rot risk alerts based on canopy humidity models, and automated deficit irrigation protocols.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

